    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> favor with those inclosed came safe. I am much
                    vexed at not hearing of <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                        Lowâ€™s</persName> draft least it should prove an inconvenience to him. I do
                    not know how to address him for I suppose he is set out, <sic>if you write let
                        know</sic> I shall be glad to hear from him often: &amp; if He will put me
                    in the way the order shall be paid in my absence. if sent after me to <placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName> I will direct the payment here. a box of
                        <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0004">my Tours</title>
                    </bibl> &amp;
                        <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0008">voyages</title>
                    </bibl> will be
                    sent to y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> care. be so good to disperse them as
                    directed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>I am D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Sir <lb/>yr obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>
                    </salute>
                    <signed>
                        <persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant </persName>
                    </signed>
                    <placeName ref="pl0699">London</placeName>
                </closer>
                <dateline>April 19<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. 1774.</dateline>

                <postscript>
                    <p>I leave town next week: but shall be some time in getting home.</p>
                </postscript>

            </div>
            <div>
                <p>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>To</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Paton</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Custom House</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Edinburgh</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </p>
            </div>
